Two newsletter issues in one entry for 1989

The Anadromous Fish Law Memo is an aperiodic publication of the Lewis and Clark Law School's Natural Resources Law Institute supported in part by the OSU Sea Grant Program. The following cover articles are in these issues: Issue 48: Native Fishing Rights and Environmental Protection in North America and New Zealand: A Comparative Analysis; Issue 49: Pluralism and the Environment: The Role of Comment Agencies in NEPA Litigation.
